{
  "stem": "13313.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Rushing towards the highway.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The, the Allies are on the highway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I-- I, I'm outside, and I'm running to this highway as well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Until this day, I remember that site.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Three Canadian tanks, Canadian tanks, on the highway going north.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the people, local people, all cheering and, and, and throwing flowers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in front of each turret there was a German prisoner with his hands up in the air like this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the chap in the turret, the driver, used to have a gun in the guy's back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Only many, many years later, when I was active in the local community and, and, and organized all kinds of celebration of the liberation, and I met the chiefs of staff of the greater Armed Forces-- I remember the Major General Fleury was the head of the Quebec command.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I told them this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, there was a reason.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they had these Germans up there to protect the driver from German snipers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't realize that at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Those-- the Canadians were absolutely reckless.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And not-- they were-- those three tanks were like, about half an hour ahead-- there was little resistance on that highway-- of the other troops.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I heard-- found out later that when they reached a, a place called the Albert Canal, which is a canal that runs past Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When they went over the bridge, the Germans lay in waiting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as soon as they went over the bridge, the Germans bombed the bridge.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they-- they were destroyed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't make it past.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they were the Canadians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when I went back home, I was so happy with this liberation that I threw my-- I had a cap-- my cap in the air.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
